on The bookkeeping obligation is subject to farmers and foresters who manage an agricultural and forestry business as owners, tenants, usufructuary or other beneficial owners, as well as lessors who run a business as a whole have leased but not given up if the requirements of Section 140 AO are met or one of the accounting limits set out in Section 141 Paragraph 1 AO is exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "When making the assessment, care must be taken to ensure that businesses that are required to keep accounts in accordance with Section 141 (1) AO are informed in good time of the start of the accounting obligation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "If the accounting obligation is no longer required, Section 141 (2) AO does not provide for a formal notification, but in these cases a corresponding note in the tax assessment or a special notification is considered appropriate for reasons of legal certainty"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "For the rest, reference is made to the following instructions regarding the accounting obligation in agricultural and forestry operations: Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 18 12 80 - S-2230 / S-0311 A - St 34 2 / St 42 1 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "1 - Rdvfgen vom 27 4 and 26 5 81 - S-2230 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 7 and \u00a7 13 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "5 - Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 13 1 82 - S-0311 / S-2163 A - St 42 1 - Tz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 15 to \u00a7 13 Section 127 EStR 1987 12 Livestock assessment For the assessment of livestock - with the exception of horses - those with Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "of 26 5 67 - S-2132 a A - St 32 2 - established average values"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "For horses acquired by the taxpayer or born in the taxpayer's business after the beginning of the 1980/81 financial year, the horses listed in the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 24 3 81 - S-2132 a A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: card 6 to \u00a7 13 - contained values \u200b\u200bare decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Incidentally also Section 125 EStR 1987 13 lump sums for personal consumption and meals The last with my Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 8 3 82 - S-2132 a A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 1a to \u00a7 13 - fixed lump sums for own consumption and the meals at book-keeping farmers were checked within the scope of this year's surveys"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "It was found that generally applicable lump sums that can be used on a broad basis in practice can no longer be determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "This is primarily due to the fact that, due to the specialization of the farms in certain branches of production, the earlier, extensive self-sufficiency of the peasant family is almost no longer to be found today"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The ones with o"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The fixed lump sums are therefore to be applied for the last time for the 1986/87 marketing year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "I ask, o"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "and to attach a corresponding handwritten note to card 1a for section 13 of the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "14 Evaluation of plant stocks in tree nurseries For the assessment of plant stocks in tree nurseries, the in the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 23 5 86 - S-2163 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 2a to \u00a7 13 - approved simplification regulations essential"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "15 Treatment of rental and commercial buildings as voluntary business assets The decision as to whether a bookkeeping farmer and forestry manager can treat a property as voluntary business assets on which a residential and commercial building is to be built for the purpose of renting out to third parties is based on the information in Sect. 14 Paragraph 3 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "5-6 EStR 1987 to meet the principles laid down"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "16 Value in use of the apartment 161 General The income from agriculture and forestry includes until the last application of Section 13 Paragraph 2 No. 2 EStG (reference to Section 52 Paragraph 15 EStG and the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 21 11 86 - S-2236 A - St 31 1 - ESt-Kartei: card 3 to \u00a7 52 EStG) also the value in use of the taxpayer's apartment, if the apartment does not exceed the size usual for businesses of the same type"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The profit of the financial year in which the value-in-use taxation ceases to apply, including the value in use still to be assessed for part of the financial year, is to be divided proportionally in accordance with Section 4a (2) No. 1 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The rental value is to be regularly estimated in analogous application of Section 8 (2) EStG, whereby the local average rent for apartments of a comparable type, location and equipment (market rent) is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "If the rental value is determined according to the rent index drawn up by the tax office,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "still to take into account the rural conditions accordingly, as far as these have not yet been given special consideration in the rent index"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In addition, agricultural holdings in the narrower sense (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "regularly not in the case of special uses) by the BFH jurisprudence (judgments of 30 1 74 - BStBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "1974 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "608 of 30 1 74 - BStBl 1975 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "3 and from 28 3 74 - BStBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "1975 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "9) to undertake approved deductions from the rental value, provided these have not yet been reflected in the rent index"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Deductions are regularly considered because of the general value-reducing factors resulting from membership in agriculture (20 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": ") and because of the special circumstances impairing the value of the individual case (up to 30 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The general discount of 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "of the rental value customary in the area is not to be made in the case of businesses with special uses, wine-growing or horticultural businesses in a normal location (see Section II No. 17 of the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 8 9 87 - S-2319 A - St 31 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In addition, reference is made to Section 130 a Paragraph 8 EStR 1987"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "162 Fair measure for 1986 in the event of an application for the abolition of the value-in-use taxation in accordance with Section 52 (15) sentence 4 EStG The highest tax authorities have decided that farmers and foresters who, by the query in line 60 of Annex L to the 1986 income tax return, should be allowed before the end of the 1987 calendar year have made a decision on the continuation or discontinuation of the value-in-use taxation until the tax assessment for 1987 becomes final; the tax assessment for 1986 is possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "to change according to \u00a7 174 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "2 Determination of profits by comparing operating income with operating expenses 21 General Because of the scope of the determination of profits according to Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG, I refer to Section 127 Paragraph 3 EStR 1987 (cf. a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Section 17 EStR 1987)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "22 Average livestock values \u200b\u200bThe average assessment permitted for bookkeeping farmers and foresters (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "12) can also be used in accordance with Section 125 a of the Income Tax Act 1987 under certain conditions when determining profits in accordance with Section 4 Paragraph 3 Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "23 Value in use of the apartment In the cases of Section 4 (3) EStG, the value in use of the apartment is to be determined in accordance with the principles applicable to accounting operations (see Sect"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "24 Maintaining the special register in accordance with Section 7a, Paragraph 8 of the Income Tax Act When determining profits in accordance with Section 4, Paragraph 3 of the Income Tax Act, special depreciation in accordance with Section 76 of the EStDV is permitted for the first time for the depreciable assets acquired or manufactured in accordance with Section 26 6 82; their use requires records in accordance with Section 7a (8) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "These records in the special directory named in Section 7a (8) of the Income Tax Act must be made at the latest by the submission of the tax return for the financial year in which the beneficial asset was acquired or manufactured"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "It is not sufficient if the directory is only available at the time of a later application after submitting the tax return, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "a later tax audit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "3 Appraisal farmers 31 General In the case of farmers and foresters who are obliged to keep accounts but do not keep proper books, the profit must be estimated in individual cases in accordance with Section 162 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to those farmers and foresters who are not obliged to keep accounts nor meet the requirements of Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 and 3 EStG if they do not have any books in the sense of"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 4 Abs 1 EStG and also the operating income and expenses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "of Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG (Section 127 Paragraph 2 - 4 EStR 1987)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The estimate has - with the exception of the in Section 127 Paragraph 4 S."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "6 second half-sentence of the EStR 1987 - to be carried out according to the principles of Section 4 (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "When making the estimate, all circumstances must be taken into account that are important for the estimate in individual cases (Section 162 (1) sentence 2 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The aim of the estimate must be to determine the profit actually achieved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Of several possible estimation methods (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Asset growth calculation, total monetary transaction calculation or estimate based on the results of similar accounting operations) is therefore the one that comes closest to the result that would have been shown in proper accounting"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In doing so, preference should always be given to the method that best takes into account the particular operational conditions of the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The uncertainties inherent in an estimate are, however, at the expense of the taxpayer, who himself gave cause for the estimate by neglecting his tax cooperation obligations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "It is important to ensure that farmers who are required to keep accounts and whose profit is estimated are to be reported to the tax auditor if an audit appears suitable or promises success for other reasons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "This applies in particular to all agricultural businesses that have fulfilled their accounting obligations for some time, then no longer keep books and allow themselves to be valued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "If a tax audit is planned in these cases, the assessment must be carried out subject to the review (Section 164 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "32 Maintaining the special register in accordance with Section 7a (8) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) Insofar as agricultural operations that are required to keep accounts and do not keep books use special depreciation in accordance with Article 76 of the Income Tax Act (EStDV), the time at which the special register in accordance with Article 7a (8) of the EStG Tz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "24 to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "33 Estimation of the profit according to standard rates It is basically left to the discretion of the tax office which estimation method it uses in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, however, the profit will have to be estimated based on the results of similar accounting operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The basis for this is a modified guideline rate estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "If, in individual cases, an estimate tailored to the particular operational conditions is not to be preferred or other empirical rates are not available, the profit can be estimated as follows: Initial estimate (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, 