tdown and suspension of delivery of reference quantities was most recently regulated by the Rdvfgen of 20 1 88 and 12 4 88 - S-2132 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: cards 18 c and d to \u00a7 13"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Corresponding fees are to be determined in individual cases on the basis of the relevant documents and added to the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "334 Value in use of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "16 to determine the principles contained"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The (gross) rental value is always to be applied, because in the profit estimate the expenses associated with the apartment - with the exception of debt interest (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "336) and the increased deductions (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "3372) - when determining the estimated starting amounts (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "331) are taken into account and thus paid for"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "335 Wage expenses For the initial estimate (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "331) it is assumed that the company is managed exclusively with unpaid workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses are therefore to be deducted from the initial estimate insofar as they relate to the profit settled with the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "If profits are recorded as a surcharge through individual calculation, care must be taken to ensure that any proportionate wage expenditure is not recorded twice (cf. in particular no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "3332 and 3333)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "336 Lease expenses, interest owed, permanent charges These expenses can be deducted insofar as they represent operating expenses and have not already been taken into account in a surcharge calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "337 other surcharges and reductions 3371 other surcharges"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Expert fees, breeding premiums, profits from the sale of fixed assets, profits from participation in cooperatives, stud fee income, feed money income, wages and remuneration for other services)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as such facts are determined in individual cases - especially in the context of company audits -"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "to make a profit surcharge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "3372 Increased deductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7 7b EStG and increased deductions according to \u00a7\u00a7 82a, 82g and 82i EStDV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "As far as increased deductions are used, the profit must be increased again by the depreciation already taken into account in the initial estimate according to Section 7 (4) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "3373 Special depreciation according to \u00a7 76 EStDV Special depreciation according to \u00a7 76 EStDV can also be deducted from the initial estimate if the relevant requirements are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "However, after the benefit period of three financial years has expired, the initial estimate must be increased by a surcharge, as, in accordance with Section 7a (9) of the Income Tax Act, the residual value is the assessment basis for further deductions for wear and tear and otherwise excessive depreciation amounts would otherwise be taken into account by applying the initial estimate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The surcharge for a financial year results from the total of the special depreciation granted divided by the remaining useful life of the respective asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The increase in the estimated amount must be carried out for the period of the remaining useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "When using the preferential treatment for immovable assets with a useful life of more than 30 years as well as for conversions and extensions to these assets, a correction is not necessary in view of Section 76 (4) sentence 3 EStDV for reasons of simplification"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In order to ensure that the surcharges are also taken into account in future assessments, the control sheet on form no. \"ESt 7\" must be kept and attached to the income tax files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "34 Standard sales rates The standard sales rates applicable for the 1987/88 financial year are set out in paragraph"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "331 printed overview of the estimated starting amounts for the respective types of business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "35 Form For the profit estimation according to the method described in paragraph"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "33 is available to the tax offices using the \"ESt 6\" form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "4 Determination of profits according to average rates (\u00a7 13a EStG) 41 General A determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry according to the average rates of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 to 8 EStG n"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "is to be carried out for the first time for financial years beginning after 30 6 80"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "For further details, I refer to the following arrangements: Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 18 12 80 - S-2230 / S-0311 A - St 34 2 / St 42 1 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "2 - Rdvfgen vom 27 4 and 26 5 81 - S-2230 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 7 to \u00a7 13 - No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "2 - Sections 127 and 130 a of the 1987 EStR In the assessment, particular attention must be paid to the fact that the relevant taxpayers are informed in good time if the prerequisites for determining profits according to average rates cease to exist (Section 13a (1) sentence 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The scheme for the determination of the profit according to \u00a7 13a Abs 3 to 8 EStG results from the form \"Appendix ESt 2L / 3L (88) - Determination of profit according to \u00a7 13a EStG\""}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "42 Profits from special uses Pursuant to Section 13a (8) No. 1 EStG, profits from special uses must also be included in the average rate under the conditions specified there"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Any loss resulting from Section 13a (8) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) must be offset against the average rate profit in accordance with Section 13a (3) to (7) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The exemption of max"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "3000 DM is only to be taken into account if the sum of the profits according to \u00a7 13a Abs 8 EStG is positive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The granting of the exemption cannot lead to a loss or change a loss"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the profits to be recognized in accordance with Section 13a (8) of the Income Tax Act are generally to be determined by comparing the operating income and the operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "For the determination of the profit from viticulture, I refer to the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 25 7 88 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Card 8 h to \u00a7 13 - and because of the determination of the profit from fruit and vegetable growing, the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 11 1 89 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: card 9 g to \u00a7 13 - to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "As far as profits from closure and severance distilleries can be determined, I ask that the responsible agricultural BP agency be involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "This will inform the taxable district of the necessary reference rates and key figures"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "43 Profits from other business operations Profits from sales of breeding cattle that exceed normal profit are to be recorded within the framework of Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The additional profits from the sale of breeding cattle must continue to be determined according to the previous procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The decisive starting values \u200b\u200bfor the 1987/88 financial year are: for breeding horses 9000 DM for riding horses 7000 DM for breeding bulls 5300 DM for breeding cows 2300 DM for breeding cattle 2200 DM for breeding sows1000 DM for breeding sows1000 DM for breeding sheep surcharge is DM1300"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "of the sales (auction) proceeds exceeding the initial values"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "5 Miscellaneous 51 Determination of capital gains - taxation of land gains I would like to draw your attention once again to the correct and timely recording of sales and land gains"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In particular, I ask that the control material available, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Notices of sale of the real estate transfer tax offices to be evaluated promptly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "52 Partial old-age benefits 521 General If partial old-age benefits exist due to farm handover contracts between parents and children not only consist of benefits in kind and in kind, it must be checked in each individual case whether the individual partial benefits are annuities or permanent expenses (recurring payments) (see BFH judgment of 28 7 83 BStBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "97)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Because of the transitional and adjustment regulations for existing old age contracts, reference is made to the Rdvfgen of 16 8 84 and 24 1 85 - S-2255 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Karte 12 and 12a to \u00a7 13"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "522 Benefits in the case of business lease agreements On the application of the BFH case law on partial retirement benefits in agriculture and forestry (judgment of 28 7 83 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": ") For so-called business leasing contracts, I refer to the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 20 5 86 - S-2255 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: card 20 to \u00a7 13 - towards"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "523 Retirement apartment after discontinuation of the value-in-use taxation If an apartment is left on the basis of a retirement contract, the value in use of the apartment - if Section 13 (2) No. 2 and Section 13a (3) No. 4 and Paragraph 7 EStG are no longer applied - is not a permanent burden for the retired person obliged to pay According to Section 10 (1) no.1a EStG, to be recorded as recurring remuneration within the meaning of Section 22 (1) sentence 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "This results from the abolition of the taxation of the value in use of the owner-occupied apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand - according to the principles of the BFH judgment of 30 10 84 BStBl 1985 II S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "610 - in the case of the pensioner, such expenses associated with the provision of the apartment are deductible as a permanent burden, which accrue to the pensioner as recurring benefits in kind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In particular, expenses for electricity, heating, water and - provided it is not a conditional usufruct in rem - cosmetic repairs are to be recorded; however, deductions for wear and tear and interest are not to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "53 Demarcation of commercial operations from agriculture and forestry 531 Purchase of third-party products According to the BFH judgment of 27 11 80 - BStBl 1981 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "518 - the answer to the question of whether the trade in self-produced gardening products and with purchased goods is to be assessed as a whole as part of a single operation as agriculture and forestry or as a commercial activity depends on the ratio of the turnover of self-produced and purchased goods to the total turnover"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Section 135 (4) EStR, on the other hand, is based on the ratio of the purchase value of third-party products to total sales"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "After a decision by the highest tax authorities of the federal states, the regulation in Section 135 (4) EStR continues to apply for reasons of simplification"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "532 Horse keeping Because of the classification of horse keeping as an agricultural or commercial activity, I refer to the evaluation of the Rdvfgen from 26 11 1981 u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "24 9 1984 - S-3110 A - St 44 2 / St 45 2 - Bew- card index: \u00a7 33 BewG horse keeping card 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In addition to Section 135 (11) of the EStR, the instructions contained therein are also to be applied mutatis mutandis to the income tax delimitation of these businesses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "54 Simplification regulation for farm handovers to family members within a financial year In the case of farm handovers to family members within a financial year, the with Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "vom 23 10 1980 - S-2239 A - St 34 2 - ESt-Kartei: Map 5 to \u00a7 13 - the regulation made to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "55 Lease of an agricultural and forestry business per parcel The lessor can only choose to continue the business if and for as long as all essential operational bases are leased to one tenant or individually to several tenants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "If the Stpfl does not clearly express his choice, the previous business assets must be continued as such as long as this is legally possible, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "how the assets are objectively suitable for resuming and continuing the discontinued operation (BFH judgment of 15 10 1987 BStBl 1988 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "260)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Furthermore, a continuation of the business is to be assumed in any case if the lessor declares that the business will not be given up but - by whoever - is to be continued at a later point in time and that there are objective circumstances in favor of the later continuation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "An objective fact speaks for the later continuation of the business if the business is not dissolved in its essential bases by the lease"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "This is the case as long as the essential economic goods are not finally used outside of the country or outside of the forest and the farmstead - in particular the farm buildings - are retained without any significant structural changes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "It also speaks in favor of maintaining the essential fundamentals of the business if the lease agreements with all tenants have a uniform duration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "If, according to the given circumstances, it is not clear whether the lessor has given up the business or continued it, the tax office (especially in the case of leasing the business in parcels) must clarify by requesting a written declaration of abandonment or continuation of the business, whether the taxpayer has given up the business or continues want to see (see Sect. 139 para 5 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "7 EStR 1987)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "56 Forestry 561 Acquisition of forest land In Section 212 (1) EStR 1987, for reasons of simplification, it is permitted that capitalized acquisition or production costs for standing wood are reduced by 3% annually"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "can be reduced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "When acquiring forest land and when acquiring businesses and sub-businesses, the purchase price must therefore be properly divided between the land and the stocking (standing wood)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Whether this has happened in individual cases is checked by the forestry expert from the regional tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "I therefore ask you to report to the regional finance directorate in the relevant cases before carrying out the assessment, enclosing the files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "562 Selling of forest land Even with the sale of forest land and the sale of businesses and sub-businesses, appropriate taxation is usually only guaranteed if the proceeds from the sale relate to the land (loss clause under Section 55 (6) EStG) and to the Tillering as well as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "on other assets (buildings, inventory, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": ") is divided"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The distribution of the sales proceeds and, if applicable,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In such cases, the corresponding book value is determined by the forestry expert from the regional finance directorate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "I therefore ask that in each individual case, immediately after a sale becomes known (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "by means of a notification of sale from the real estate acquisition tax office) and before carrying out the corresponding assessment, enclosing the tax files and the standard value files of the regional finance office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "563 Tariff reduction according to \u00a7 34b EStG Applications for the application of the reduced tax rates according to \u00a7 34b EStG for extraordinary income from forestry (extraordinary use of wood and wood use as a result of force majeure - calamity use -) must be forwarded immediately to the regional tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "After a review by the forestry expert, the tax offices receive a notification about the amount of tax-privileged wood use, which must be taken into account in the assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "57 Control reports Except in the usual cases (control reports for the purposes of Bp, inheritance tax, wage tax, unit valuation, etc.)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "), particularly in the case of lease / usage relationships, control notifications must be prepared using the \"ESt 34 d\" form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The cases in which the individual lease / use ratio comprises agricultural areas of more than 2 ha or in which areas with special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "of Section 13a Paragraph 4 No. 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "I ask that incoming control reports as well as unit value reports always be evaluated promptly because of possible effects on the way in which the taxpayer's profit is determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "When evaluating them, it can be useful to consult the standard value files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The same also applies to the assessment of farmers and foresters, particularly when determining profits in accordance with Section 13a of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "58 Amendments to the Income Tax Act by the Tax Reform Act 1990 that were already applied to the income tax assessment or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Determination of profits for calendar years prior to 1990 must be observed 581 transitional regulations for owner-occupied apartments in the business assets of a farmer and forestry manager (Section 52 (15) EStG) According to Section 52 (15) sentence 3 EStG, a farmer and forestry worker who is working on an agricultural and forestry business can Property belonging to business assets, built an apartment for their own residential purposes or an apartment for the elderly that will only be completed after December 31, 1986, continue to record the value in use of the apartment as part of the profit determination up to and including the assessment period 1998"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for this is that the building application was submitted before 1 1 1987 and that the apartment is used for the taxpayer's own residential purposes or for the residential purposes of the senior citizen in the year of completion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "This now also covers the cases in which the building application was submitted between 28 2 1986 and 1 1 1987"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "582 Tax-free withdrawal of land from agricultural and forestry business assets According to the newly inserted sentence 10 of Section 52 (15) EStG, a farmer and forester can after 31 12 1986 land his agricultural and forestry business assets by building with a Take out an apartment for your own residential purposes or an apartment that is shared between the elderly and tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "This regulation applies accordingly to real estate that in the assessment period 1986 still belonged to commercial assets or business assets used for self-employed work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "583 Benefit in the case of severance payments to heirs and the repayment of debts in agriculture and forestry (Section 14a EStG) The benefits contained in Section 14a (4) and (5) EStG for the sale or removal of agricultural and forestry land to compensate for replacement heirs or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "for debt repayment in agriculture and forestry are dependent on compliance with certain income limits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Here sliding rules have now been introduced which, if the relevant income limits are exceeded, lead to a step-by-step reduction in the tax exemptions in the event of compensation for heirs who have given way and in the event of debt repayment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "The new regulations are already to be applied to sales and withdrawals made after December 31, 1985 (Section 52 (17) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the exemption for debt repayment under paragraph 5 will be extended by four years until the end of 1992"}, {"meta": {"name": "0090691.xml"}, "text": "Income tax / wage tax / church tax Invoicing Procedural law / tax code Commercial law Corporate law Rhineland-Palatinate Agriculture Income tax Farmer"}]